{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Reaper Item Quick Settings GUI\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Prerequisits:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ReaImGui (cfillion)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Explorer Item Source Folder (Meat-Scripts)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This GUI displays controls for each selected item\u8217's first take.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Settings that can be toggled between displayed/hidden:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Name, Volume, Pan, Pitch, Play Rate, Pitch Mode, and EQ.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab EQ parameter enables the application of basic EQ curves (high pass, low pass, band pass):\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Dynamically adds/removes ReaEQ (named 'RS_EQ') to the end of the FX chain on the take.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Script supports moving the EQ instance wherever you want.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Always-displayed settings include:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Solo & Mute buttons: applies to the track of the media item.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Loop: sets timeline selection to the item, moves playhead to its start, enables 'Repeat'.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Rename: applies the text written in the 'Name' field to the take.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Source: opens windows explorer to the location of the audio file on the disk drive.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab FX: opens the FX window for the take.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Reverse: applies to the take.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Hold: keeps a given item in the GUI, regardless if it is selected or not.\sa180\par}
}

