{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Scroll Media Item to Next Variation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Given an media item with several variations separated by silence, uses peak detection to modify start offset such that it 'scrolls' the next variation to the start of the media item.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Change 'ASK_USER' variable to 'true' if you want to be prompted for peak detection thresholds when the script runs.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Recommended shortcut : CTRL+ALT+C\sa180\par}
}

